hopobject.body: I saw your advert in the paper torrance pharmacy That obviously didn't happen, as Thomas moved during the 2011-12 season and then took the next year -- his final one under contract with the B's -- off from hockey. The Bruins dealt him to the Islanders in a move that was only made to help New York reach the cap floor. Thomas then decided prior to free agency that he'd like to play this season, and after his agent left to become assistant general manager of the Blue Jackets, Thomas and his new agent secured a tryout with the Panthers that turned into a one-year contract at 39 years young.Â
